if you didnt have asthma when you were a kid can you have it now at if so what are the symptoms like everyone in my family has asthma except for my mother and i i was diagnosed with asthma when i was less than a year ago there is no history of asthma in my family otherwise asthma can happen to anyone at any time in their life common asthma symptoms are wheezing coughing for weeks or months chest tightness shortness of breath with activity coughing violently at night coughing material out of your lungs coughing or wheezing in the presence of specific substances like truck exhaust dust etc there are a variety of symptoms and triggers please talk to a doctor about what's going on with you to sort it out if you suspect that you have a problem with your lungs asthma comes with different symptoms and causes as well as different intensities my asthma changes every few months at first i took an inhaled steroid alone and that was good then i was on advair spiriva and albuterol salbutamol twice a day for a month then i went for four months using my salbutamol inhaler once or twice a week in the last week i've been started on advair again all of this is because things change and my symptoms become bad from time to time maybe i will be going back to using my rescue inhaler only in a month or so i don't know asthma is something to take very seriously the main problem i have with mine is that it changes on me if i took the maximum amount of medications that i was on all the time i would be seriously over medicated most of the time there has to be a balance found between treating symptoms and not causing the patient side effects Pneumonia Hay fever Lung cancer Salbutamol Allergy Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Cancer Stomach cancer Medicine Gastroesophageal reflux disease Mesothelioma Traumatic brain injury Aspergillosis Tuberculosis Urinary incontinence Multiple sclerosis First aid Prostate cancer Tobacco smoking Insulin Psoriasis Decompression sickness E